**CONFIDENTIAL ENGINEERING DOCUMENTATION**

# Table of Contents

# 1. Project Overview

Cloud Workstation OS (CloudWS) is an immutable, cloud-native workstation operating system built on Fedora Rawhide bootc. The project targets universal hardware compatibility across AMD, Intel, and NVIDIA platforms, deploying to bare metal, Hyper-V virtual machines, WSL2, and OCI containers. The system ships five output formats: RAW disk image, VHDX, WSL tarball, Anaconda ISO, and OCI registry push to GitHub Container Registry.

The project encompasses two major codebases. The primary codebase is the Fedora Rawhide bootc immutable OS build system, orchestrated from a Windows host via PowerShell with modular bash scripts executed inside a Podman container build. The secondary codebase, documented in this snapshot, is the CachyOS/Arch Linux virtualization host toolkit: a comprehensive suite of scripts for system profiling, VFIO GPU passthrough configuration, CPU core isolation, VM CPU pinning, Secure Boot enrollment, and unified management.

## 1.1 Architecture Evolution

CloudWS began as a CachyOS/Arch-based system using pacman and AUR packages. It subsequently migrated to Fedora Rawhide bootc for immutability guarantees, atomic updates via GHCR, and enterprise SELinux integration. The build orchestrator was rewritten from a monolithic 1,500-line PowerShell heredoc into a fully modular architecture with numbered standalone bash scripts, a shared package parser library, and a declarative PACKAGES.md manifest.

## 1.2 Core Technology Stack

| **Component** | **Technology** |
| --- | --- |
| Desktop | GNOME 50 (Wayland-only, Mutter 50, GTK 4.22, libadwaita 1.9) |
| Base OS | Fedora Rawhide bootc (fc45), dnf5, systemd, SELinux |
| Virtualization | KVM / QEMU / libvirt / VFIO GPU Passthrough |
| Containers | Podman (rootful, dedicated builder machine), K3s |
| High Availability | Pacemaker / Corosync clustering |
| Security | CrowdSec IPS (sovereign/offline), firewalld, authselect |
| Gaming | Gamescope SteamOS-mode GDM session |
| Android | Waydroid container runtime |
| Registry | GHCR (ghcr.io/kabuki94/cloudws-bootc:latest) |
| Build Host | Windows + PowerShell orchestrator + Podman machine |

## 1.3 Output Formats

| **Format** | **Deployment Target** |
| --- | --- |
| RAW disk image | Bare metal dd-write or qemu-img convert |
| VHDX | Hyper-V virtual machines on Windows hosts |
| WSL tarball | Windows Subsystem for Linux 2 import |
| Anaconda ISO | Interactive installer for traditional deployment |
| OCI push to GHCR | Atomic updates via bootc / GNOME Software |

